commit.message: Please update your links to https://sourceforge.net/projects/skfans
Release 2.15.6

Reduce max raw resource site count.

It seems like 14 is a bit much, so will go with what's in 7k2hd.

Misc: Update comment on points_distance().

There will be an issue with any even sized shape.
Use rects_distance() for more town distance calculations.

Town: Initialize statistics for new nation.

If population is left zero, then there is a small window until the next
month that the nation will immediately surrender if Nation::think_surrender()
is executed, because this is used as a defeat condition.

7k2 tried to fix this with a couple changes. It tried to switch init
order in a risky (buggy?) way, and created a work-around as well, (why?).
The probability of Nation::think_surrender() of happening under recent
event conditions should be a clue something else was amiss.
NationAI: When grant to town did work, then recruit immediately.
FirmCampAI: Don't grant town money when in debt.
NationAI: Only allow town unit training with enough cash.

Info: Block button for attack flag when spying.

7k2 has the same issue.
Vga: Handle the event SDL_RENDER_TARGETS_RESET.

Vga: Fix mouse bound checks.

When scrolling to the edge with the improper checking, this was causing a
loop of warping and mouse move events. With improvements in SDL, it
increased the load on the CPU and caused more warps per frame, making the
mouse pointer to stick to the edge longer going throught the processing.

TownAI: Use scout method that will work for different map sizes.

Also went ahead and limited the max distance to about 100 as originally.

NationAI: Finish sea based action by issuing final order.

This reenables code that appears to have been fully finished. I believe
it was disabled due to an issue late in development that caused the
final order to fail. I fixed an issue with unit move blocked by team in
the previous commit. Now when this sea code is enabled, it appears to be
working as expected.

Previously, when the AI landed the people, the action was not
necessarily ended. Eventually it could be reprocessed or reordered, but
it took some time. This fix makes the AI act immediately, which is what
we want.

Unit: Stop ordering blocking idle teammate to action destination.

This order to an idle teammate to push to the same destination only
serves to obstruct completing the action. I think there was team
movement in mind here, but if the units are not ordered to move
together, then an individual move order shouldn't be swapped to
someone else not going there.

The fix is to use the more usual block-by-idle unit resolution.
Mine: Add config setting for unlimited mine reserve.

TownAI: Pick a better direction to scout.

The original choice requires a min 50 distance in both x and y strongly
biases the move order to be exactly to a map corner, especially since
it could go up to 50 more in x and y again.

The random choice now is simply picked with-in one edge of the map
randomly which is what most people do anyway. Hopefully that improves
the change enough the AI can connect with other players very early in
the game.

NationAI: Correctly check scout action for processing.

The scout action was never properly implemented. This corrects the code
so that it will now work. It might be a good thing so the AI can do more
in the early game.

7k2 has the same problem, although I'm not sure if it matters there.
Unit: Disable the political path logic.
Update distance calculation while processing various actions.

Update AI and generation code distance measurements.

This updates AI decision making using precise measurements where needed
and also map generation. Not all AI distance measurements are updated,
as the effect of being off (like looking for a raw site) may be
negligable in practice. Anytime it is critical to linking, bldg layout,
or in battle, this is what we are changing here.

The function TownArray::find_nearest_town is not used, and it seems to
strongly imply that it is from the Capitalism game. Towns were likely
measured to their "center" being a center of town, but there were not
generated with a regular shape, so it was arbitrary. It is updated in
case it does get used again in 7k.

Switch distance calculation used for firm and town linking.

When placing alternating firms and towns, the points_distance() function
is called with the center x,y member variables to link the towns. This
produces an effect that depending on the side of the town, the max
distance between firms and towns changes. If you want towns to link for
management purposes, you have to squeeze them together closer, meaning a
very cramped layout or only building in a single line of towns and firms.

The change here makes the distance consistent on all sides of the town,
linking as expected during game play.

Misc: Add rects_distance() function.

This function can be used over the points_distance() function when
dealing with rectangular shaped objects in an integer coordinate system.
This will handle finding a center coordinate that makes sense when a
precise distance from the center of an odd sized shaped to an even sized
shape is not possible.

NationAI: Prevent recruiting when there is no overseer.

Due to a logic bug, the AI could recruit civilians when the action was
to move to another town when there was no overseer and without the
minimum recruit loyalty. This would trigger rebellions. The logic is now
fixed.

7k2 has the same fix. Although using the town 'has_linked_own_camp' flag
is unreliable. The flag is updated in the town periodic processing, which
may not happen before the recruit logic is processed. However this issue
is found all over the place and not as severe an issue. It maybe better
to replace these with Town::has_linked_camp(..., needOverseer=1) in the
future.

FirmMarket: Fix distance check.

Spotted this bug while stress testing code. The y axis is completely
zeroed out, which would have the effect of allowing markets unrestricted
to one half of the map, if the AI otherwise wants to. This at least keeps
the distance a little closer to home. Maybe the AI will be a little more
reasonable on building export markets.

7k2 has the same bug.

UnitGod: Improve handling case where FirmBase is destroyed already.

This is an update to cf2ab3623 where a cast power is called and the
attached firm is already destroyed. The god unit cannot cast the power
without prayer points. The firm will no longer exist, so check that it is
deleted properly before continuing.

Nation: Reduce penalty for trade unit destruction.

The penalty being applied for all nationalities is quite harsh. Reduce
the penalty to a similar level to what is found in 7k2. Hopefully this
can prevent more instances where the AI collapses quickly late game.

The method NationBase::civilian_killed is cleaned up further for
clarity.
Spy: Fix premature dereference.

UnitMarine: Don't give move order when the ship is still docked.

This happens when the trade ship is manually docked and only has one stop.
Hide the register keyword if the compiler does not support it.
